The paper discusses the strategic behavior of processors in shard-based consensus protocols, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also uses game theory to analyze the behavior of processors, which falls under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). The paper proposes a mechanism to promote cooperation among processors, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed). Finally, the paper uses numerical results to support its claims, which involves machine learning (cs.LG).
